A Durban man is recovering in hospital after he was shot during
an alleged altercation Meller Road in Pinetown. Shawn Herbst, Netcare 911 spokesperson said the incident
happened just after 10.30 am on Tuesday. He said reports indicate that a man suffered a single
gunshot wound to his abdomen while at the intersection. “It was alleged by members of the public that an altercation
had broken out when the shot was fired,” said Herbst. The man was in a serious condition and was taken to hospital. Herbst said circumstances leading up to the event will be
investigated by the Pinetown SAPS who were on scene.